Java Calculator

Description
This Java application implements a basic calculator with GUI using Swing. It performs simple arithmetic operations (+, -, *, /), includes decimal point functionality, and supports clearing, deleting, and negating numbers.

Features
Arithmetic Operations: Addition (+), Subtraction (-), Multiplication (*), Division (/).
Decimal Point: Allows input of decimal numbers.
Clear and Delete: Clears the input field (Clr), deletes the last character (Del).
Negative Number: Negates the current number ((-)).
Responsive GUI: User-friendly interface using Swing components.

How to Use
Run the Calculator class.
Enter numbers using the numeric keypad.
Use the arithmetic buttons (+, -, *, /) to perform operations.
Press . for decimal points.
Use Clr to clear the input field and Del to delete the last character.
Press (-) to negate the current number.
Press = to display the result of the operation.

Technologies Used
Java
Swing (for GUI)

Contributions
Contributions to enhance the calculator's features or fix issues are welcome. Please fork the repository and create a pull request.
